Imports & Setup                                                                                                                                                    
tkinter → GUI (buttons, labels, windows)
random → randomly choose coins
json → save/load game progress
time → for auto-mining updates
dataclasses → manage game data neatly

Game Data
RARITIES → coin types (Common, Rare, Legendary, etc.)
ASSETS → auto-mining machines you can buy
UPGRADES → upgrades (luck & power)
SAVE_FILE_DEFAULT → default save file
TICK_MS → game loop interval (10 updates/sec)
Helper Functions
weighted_choice → randomly chooses item based on weight
format_money → formats large numbers (1,000 → 1K)

Game State
Stores player progress: balance, inventory, assets, upgrades
Tracks mines per click, total mined, auto-mining buffer

Methods:
total_mines_per_sec() → calculates auto-mining rate
luck_multiplier() → luck from upgrades
value_multiplier() → coin value multiplier from uprades

Main Game Class (CryptoMinerGame)
Sets up GUI and game loop using ttk.Frame
GUI Construction
Top bar: balance, mining rate, total mined, save/load/reset
Left panel: Mine button, sell coins, inventory list
Middle panel: Assets (buy auto-miners), Upgrades (luck & power)
Right panel: Info/instructions
Status bar: shows game messages

Mining Mechanics
roll_coin(mines) → randomly chooses coins based on luck
grant_drops(drops) → adds coins to inventory
mine_click() → triggered by MINE button
auto_mine_tick(dt_sec) → auto-mines coins per second
coins_value() → calculates total coin value
sell_all() → converts inventory to balance

Shop Mechanics
asset_cost(key) → calculates asset cost
buy_asset(key) → buy assets and deduct balance
upgrade_cost(key) → calculates upgrade cost
buy_upgrade(key) → buy upgrades and deduct balance

UI Updates
refresh_inventory_box() → updates coin inventory list
_update_all_labels() → updates all labels and buttons

Game Loop
_schedule_tick() → schedules tick every 100ms
_tick() → auto-mines, updates GUI, reschedules next tick

Save / Load / Reset
save() → saves game state to JSON
load() → loads game state from JSON
reset_confirm() → resets progress after confirmation

Main Function
main() → initializes Tkinter window and starts game loop

Gameplay Summary
Click MINE or buy assets for auto-mining
Collect coins of varying rarities
Sell coins to get balance
Buy upgrades to improve luck or coin value
Save/load progress
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Main Window
tk.Tk() creates the main window
Sets title and minimum size

Main Frame
ttk.Frame as the main container
Expands in all directions (sticky="nsew")

Top Bar
Horizontal frame at the top
Contains:
Balance (self.balance_var)
Mining rate (self.rate_var)
Total mines (self.mined_var)
Buttons: Save, Load, Reset

Main Columns
Frame holding three columns:
Left: Mining section
Middle: Shop (Assets + Upgrades)
Right: Info panel

Left Panel – Mining
ttk.LabelFrame titled “Mining”
Contains:
Mine button (⛏️ MINE)
Sell button (💰 Sell Coins)
Inventory Listbox showing collected coins

Middle Panel – Shop
Assets (LabelFrame): auto-mining machines
Each row: asset name, info label (owned, cost, per second), buy button
Upgrades (LabelFrame): Luck Booster, Power Upgrade
Each row: upgrade name, info label (level, cost, effect), buy button

Right Panel – Info
LabelFrame titled “Info”
Text widget for instructions and information (scrollable, multi-line)

Status Bar
Label at the bottom showing game messages
Linked to StringVar() (self.status_var)

Button States & Labels
Buttons enable/disable based on balance
Inventory Listbox dynamically updated
Labels linked to StringVar() for automatic updates

Layout Strategy
Uses grid system (row, column, sticky)
columnconfigure and rowconfigure to allow resizing
LabelFrame groups related widgets
Padding (padx, pady) for clean layout

UI Summary
Top Bar – balance, rate, total, save/load/reset
Left Column – Mining & Inventory
Middle Column – Assets (top) and Upgrades (bottom)
Right Column – Info text box
Bottom – Status bar
